Application Setup - When app starts
server.js
  ↓
loads .env
  ↓
loads app.js
  ↓
loads db.js
  ↓
connects to MongoDB
  ↓
starts server on PORT 3000



Request Flow - When a request comes in
client sends request
  ↓
app.js receives request
  ↓
express.json() reads the JSON body
  ↓
/notes route catches the request
  ↓
authenticateJWT middleware checks the token
  ↓
createNote controller handles the logic
  ↓
Note model talks to MongoDB
  ↓
MongoDB saves the note
  ↓
controller sends response back

Auth flow
1. models/User.js
  1. defines what a user looks like in MongoDB
2. controllers/authController.js
  1. registerUser  
  2. loginUser
3. routes/authRoutes.js
  1. POST /register  
  2. POST /login
4. middlewares/authMiddleware.js
  1. protects private routes later
5. app.js mounts /auth
  1. mounts auth routes with app.use("/auth", authRoutes)